Analysis of Line Skaters

This is a NHL assessment for both NHL lines and pairings
It is ordered by net points.
The tot_net_points field reflects net points for goals, shots and blocks "for" against  goals, shots and blocks "against.
#  note: there are so many columns in the file that "view" will not run them all. 
line_analysis <- read_csv("extra/Moneypuck/lines_Moneypuck/lines.csv", col_names = TRUE) %>%
  select(2:9, 25:27, 73:75) %>%
  clean_names() %>% 
  dplyr::mutate(tot_pts_goals_for = goals_for * 8.5, tot_pts_shot_attempts_for = shot_attempts_for * 1.5, tot__pts_blocked_shot_attempts_for = blocked_shot_attempts_for * 1.3, tot_points_for = tot_pts_goals_for + tot_pts_shot_attempts_for + tot__pts_blocked_shot_attempts_for, tot_pts_goals_against = goals_against * 8.5, tot_pts_shot_attempts_against = shot_attempts_against * 1.5, tot__pts_blocked_shot_attempts_against = blocked_shot_attempts_against * 1.3, tot_points_against = tot__pts_blocked_shot_attempts_against + tot_pts_shot_attempts_against + tot_pts_goals_against, tot_net_points =  tot_points_for - tot_points_against, points_for_per_60 = round((tot_points_for *60)/(icetime/60),2), points_against_per_60 = round((tot_points_against *60)/(icetime/60),2)) %>%
  dplyr::relocate(name, team, position, tot_net_points, points_for_per_60, points_against_per_60, goals_for, shot_attempts_for, blocked_shot_attempts_for) %>%
  dplyr::arrange(desc(tot_net_points), team)

NHL line data is ordered by total net points and team

      It shows seasonal data for lines and pairings
      It reflects the best lines/pairings in a hocky season.
datatable(line_analysis, class = 'cell-border stripe')
